text: Veronika Jeger (born 28 October 1969) is a road cyclist from Hungary. In 2001 and 2004 she won the Hungarian National Road Race Championships. She represented her nation at the 2004 UCI Road World Championships. ==References== ==External links== * profile at Procyclingstats.com Category:1969 births Category:Hungarian female cyclists Category:Living people Category:Place of birth missing (living people)
